flowdock-api
===========

Ruby Gem for using Flowdock public API.

* https://www.flowdock.com/help/api

Compatibility
-------------

flowdock-api has been tested under Ruby 1.8.7

Requirements
------------

* HTTParty

Install
-------

* gem install flowdock-api

Example
-------

  require 'lib/flowdock-api'

  # create a new Flow object with target flow's api token and sender information
  flow = Flowdock.new(:api_token => "56188e2003e370c6efa9711988f7bf02", 
    :source => "myapp", 
    :from => {:name => "John Doe", :address => "john.doe@yourdomain.com"})

  # send message to the flow
  flow.send_message(:subject => "Test subject", 
    :content => "<h2>Test message</h2><p>Foobar</p>", 
    :tags => ["cool", "stuff"])	
	 
API methods
-----------

* Flow methods

  send_message(params) - Send message to flow. Required parameters for message are :subject and :content. Optional parameter :tags can be used to add tags to message.


